#HairDiscrimination IS racial discrimination – and it looks like this 👆

This #CROWNDay, join the movement 👑 

Racial discrimination against hairtsyles can start as early as five years old – and last a lifetime ⚠️ From schools to the corporate world, Black people are still being denied work and educational opportunities because of their natural, textured hair and protective styles. This is unacceptable and the time to act is NOW.

👑Join the movement to #PassTheCROWN
🔗Tap the link in our bio to: ✍️ Sign the @thecrownact petition and 🇺🇸 Write or Tweet to your US Senator 
📣 Share these stories with everyone you know 

#Dove #CROWN #CROWNCoalition #NaturalHair #HairLove #CROWNAct #TheCROWNAct #BlackHair #SignThePetition #EndHairDiscrimination #EndRacialDiscrimination #RacialDiscrimination

Introducing the Let’s Change Beauty podcast with #DovePartner and cultural expert @imjessweiner 🤩 Powered by the #DoveSelfEsteemProject, #LetsChangeBeauty features intimate conversations with experts and celebrated guests on:

🙌 Redefining beauty on their own terms 
⚠️ Decoding toxic beauty advice on social media

💪 And building self-esteem in the next generation 

Tune in to hear more on @iheartmediaofficial, @applemusic or wherever you get your podcasts.

🎤 Toxic beauty advice is harming her self-esteem. We’re on a mission to change that 💙

Did you know that 1 in 2 girls say toxic beauty advice on social media causes low self-esteem?*

Our research shows just how important it is for young people to create an online space that influences them in a healthy and uplifting way 💫 Go to the 🔗 in our bio to find out how you can help young people detox their feeds today 🙌

#Dove #DoveSelfEsteemProject #DetoxYourFeed #SelfEsteem #BodyConfidence #ToxicBeauty #BeautyStandards #BeautyAdvice #LetsChangeBeauty

*Source: Dove Self-Esteem and Social Media Report (April 2022)

🎤 You wouldn’t say this to your daughter, but she could be hearing it online. Every. Single. Day.

📣 1 in 2 girls say toxic beauty advice causes low self-esteem.* 📣

This has to stop. 

Social media can be overwhelming for young people, especially when their feed is full of toxic beauty standards and trends. As part of the Dove Self-Esteem Project, we’re on a mission to tackle toxic beauty advice and help them detox their feeds – so they can grow up with the self-esteem they deserve and reach their full potential  💙

Join our movement. 
Share this post to your stories to raise awareness and head to the 🔗 in our bio to watch our guide to detox young people’s feeds together 🙏

*Source: Dove Self-Esteem and Social Media Report (April 2022)

📣 My Beauty, My Say 📣  我的美, 我说了算 

The pressure to conform to unrealistic beauty standards online is affecting people everywhere 🌎 Data shows that over 70% of women* retouch or add filters to their selfies before posting. With our new campaign, My Beauty, My Say, we’re sharing inspiring stories from women who are making a positive change and learning to love what they see in the mirror 😍

We're committed to celebrating women as they are in real life – join our movement and take the #NoDigitalDistortion Pledge at the 🔗 in bio ❤️

*In China

#Dove #RealBeauty #NoDigitalDistortion #MyBeautyMySay #BeautyIdeals #LetsChangeBeauty #SelfEsteem #SelfLove

📣 “We’re still fighting for the right to wear our hair the way that it naturally grows”

#BlackHistoryMonth is a celebration of Black voices and achievements 💪 It’s also a time for awareness and action – towards inclusivity and equity. Race-based hair discrimination can start #AsEarlyAsFive years old – and last a lifetime ❌It is unacceptable that this is still legal in many states across the US ❌

Black people should not have to conform to Eurocentric beauty standards to live, work, and exist. As co-founders of the CROWN Coalition, we’re working to make race-based hair discrimination illegal. We’re making progress, but there is still a long way to go. 

✍️ Head to our 🔗 in bio and sign @theCROWNAct petition to #PassTheCROWN 👑 in all 50 US states
📩 Download the template and write a letter to your state legislators
💪 Share, share, share 
🎬: @bustle 

#Regram #Dove #RealBeauty #NaturalHair #HairDiscrimination #TheCROWNAct #CROWNCoalition #PassTheCROWN #EndHairDiscrimination #SignThePetition #TakeAction

Introducing… the new Dove film, ‘As Early As Five’ 🎬 Based on too many true stories, it raises awareness of the shocking reality that race-based hair discrimination can start as early as five years old – and last a lifetime.

Natural Black hair and protective styles are subject to a number of discriminatory policies and are excluded from societal beauty ideals. As a result, systemic racism, bias and discrimination starts with children, affecting not only their self-esteem but their perceived self-worth in the world 🌎

This needs to change. All of our beauty should be welcomed – everywhere. Tap the 🔗 in our bio to join us and supporters across the US to take action: 
✍️ Sign @thecrownact petition to make race-based hair discrimination illegal 
👇Let your #AsEarlyAsFive story be heard by using the hashtag and tagging @Dove, or comment below 

#Dove #AsEarlyAsFive #PassTheCROWN #TheCROWNAct #CROWNCoalition #EndHairDiscrimination #BlackHairIsBeautiful #Confidence #SelfEsteem #LetsChangeBeauty
